    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate focusing heavily on exploiting the matchup against Lance McCullers Jr., where **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** leads our positional players with a 76.01 efficiency score. His profile is maximized by a favorable platoon split and a slow delivery from the opposing pitcher, which provides an ideal environment for his elite stolen base potential. **Trevor Story** remains our most potent threat despite a 34% rain risk, as his 75.93 score is anchored by a park factor boost that outweighs the volatility of the weather. **James Wood** is our premier outfield start; batting leadoff against a lefty-leaning matchup, his 73.18 score reflects the significant value of his position in the order and the favorable matchup against Hudson.\n\nWhile **Giancarlo Stanton** (65.91) and **Mickey Moniak** (64.12) are locked into strong starts due to their respective platoon advantages and speed profiles, the benching of **Seiya Suzuki** proved to be the most difficult decision. With a score of 45.02, **Seiya Suzuki** was on the fringe, but he was ultimately relegated to the bench because the optimizer prioritized the higher ceiling of **Austin Riley** (62.13) and the extreme situational value of **Jose Caballero** (58.17) in a speed-heavy context. We are monitoring the pending lineups for **Dalton Rushing**, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Jose Caballero**, and **Alex Freeland** closely; should any of these players move down the order, their efficiency scores will slide further, potentially forcing us to look toward deeper bench depth like **Kyle Karros** or **Max Muncy**, though the latter remains below our operational floor of 40.0.",
